<span id="freeTextContainer8817369890369985136">This was the first book I ever read by Ann Rule and it was the perfect true crime book. I found a battered copy at a used bookshop.<br/><br/>I inhaled this book during a Christmas break and was so intrigued how close Ann came to know Ted Bundy when she was volunteering at the suicide help line.<br/><br/>Yes he is a charismatic serial killer who targeted young women and when he got caught he denied nothing <br/><br/>This book is a modern classic. </span>

