    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1892365918" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1892365918" />
    <a title="LeAnne: GeezerMom" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7862560-leanne-geezermom"><img alt="LeAnne: GeezerMom" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514579326p2/7862560.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1892365918?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LeAnne: GeezerMom" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LeAnne: GeezerMom" href="/user/show/7862560-leanne-geezermom">LeAnne: GeezerMom</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781416559597" href="/book/show/2896442-the-stranger-beside-me">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1892365918" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14151404416535694046">I was a freshman at FSU in the fall of 1979 and had a work study job at the multimedia laboratory on campus. I worked with professionals learning about campus TV productions, photography, and journalism. Several of the people that I worked with had to go to Bundy&apos;s trial to testify for the defense. After he killed the girls at FSU&apos;s Chi Omega sorority house, it was a multi media laboratory van that he stole and drove to Lakeland where he killed his final victim and was captured.  Basically, they</span>
  <span id="freeText14151404416535694046" style="display:none">I was a freshman at FSU in the fall of 1979 and had a work study job at the multimedia laboratory on campus. I worked with professionals learning about campus TV productions, photography, and journalism. Several of the people that I worked with had to go to Bundy's trial to testify for the defense. After he killed the girls at FSU's Chi Omega sorority house, it was a multi media laboratory van that he stole and drove to Lakeland where he killed his final victim and was captured.  Basically, they wanted to ask everyone if they happened to own a pair of Levi's 501 jeans and might have worn them while traveling in the van. Those were the kinds of fibers that were discovered, and the defense was trying to weaken the prosecution's case against Bundy.<br /><br />When the trial was over and they were free to speak about it, they were pretty shaken.   Until I saw somebody's status update today, I had forgotten all about this book. For obvious reasons, I loved it - trying to unravel the twisted mind of this man is something that can never be accomplished, but having lived on campus that year and seeing everyone wearing "Burn Bundy" tshirts, it was a book I had to read. True crime is generally not my genre of choice, but this writer is excellent. I read a few of her other works and appreciate the details she put into her stories. Truth is far stranger than fiction.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14151404416535694046" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

