<div id="review_2214592294" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2214592294" />
    <a title="☮Karen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1076079-karen"><img alt="☮Karen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627237140p2/1076079.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2214592294?book_show_action=true">Dec 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="☮Karen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="☮Karen" href="/user/show/1076079-karen">☮Karen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1076079-karen?shelf=library-checkout">library-checkout</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1076079-karen?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1076079-karen?shelf=book-club">book-club</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1076079-karen?shelf=hoopla">hoopla</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1076079-karen?shelf=read-in-2018">read-in-2018</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2214592294" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12407359859415696898">In person book club read #12.<br/><br/>I can&apos;t wait to talk about this one with the gals in the bookclub. I&apos;ve always been fascinated by Ted Bundy, and actually think I read this before right after it was first published. Now I&apos;m again a little obsessed, watching his interviews on youtube, and on Hoopla watched the made-for-TV movie based on this book. Very good!<br/><br/>I clearly remember when Bundy was electrocuted for 36 murders, all young attractive women, many killed in their college rooms as they slept. I wa</span>
  <span id="freeText12407359859415696898" style="display:none">In person book club read #12.<br /><br />I can't wait to talk about this one with the gals in the bookclub. I've always been fascinated by Ted Bundy, and actually think I read this before right after it was first published. Now I'm again a little obsessed, watching his interviews on youtube, and on Hoopla watched the made-for-TV movie based on this book. Very good!<br /><br />I clearly remember when Bundy was electrocuted for 36 murders, all young attractive women, many killed in their college rooms as they slept. I was in college at that time. (He probably killed more than 100.)<br /><br />I remember the people outside while Bundy was being executed, chanting, "It's FRY day, Bundy." <br /><br />Girls who fit his type cried and grieved him. <br /><br />Will probably add to this later.<br /><br />UPDATE:<br />Following our book club discussion, I decided to change my rating from 5 stars to 4. It is the story of Ted Bundy we all find fascinating, but not necessarily this particular book or Ann Rule's writing. This book did have, like most true crime books, an awful lot of minutiae, listing every lawyer involved, every witness, every judge, etc., which is why I don't usually read true crime as a rule (no pun intended). So 4 stars and we really did have a great discussion on this last weekend. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12407359859415696898" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


